\lang english
Security Awareness and Training Policy
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "pol:2.03"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Policy Metadata

\lang english
Effective:
 July 01,
 2026
\begin_inset space \hfill{}
\end_inset

Version:
 1.0
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy defines the mandatory requirements for the Elko County Security Awareness and Training Program.
 It ensures that all personnel with access to County Information Technology (IT) resources possess the requisite knowledge to protect information assets,
 reduce operational risk,
 and maintain strict compliance with the FBI Criminal Justice Information Services (CJIS) Security Policy and Nevada Revised Statutes (NRS).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County personnel—
including full-time and part-time employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 interns,
 and volunteers—
who meet any of the following criteria:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Possess logical access to any County-managed information system or network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Possess unescorted physical access to areas designated as Physically Secure Locations (e.g.,
 server rooms,
 dispatch centers).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Process,
 store,
 or transmit Criminal Justice Information (CJI) or Personally Identifiable Information (PII).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall Serve as the final Authorizing Official (AO) for the training curriculum.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall review and update training content at least annually to align with CJIS v6.0 and NIST standards.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall develop and provide the technical training content to Human Resources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall conduct technical practical exercises (e.g.,
 spear-phishing simulations).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall proactively "push" emerging threat alerts to the workforce.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Human Resources (HR)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the Program Manager for general security literacy and must:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Schedule,
 track,
 and document completion of the General Security Awareness curriculum for all personnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Prohibit the onboarding or credentialing of any personnel until initial training is verified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Enforce administrative actions for personnel who fail to meet annual refresher deadlines.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure 100% of their assigned personnel complete training within the mandated windows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall enforce immediate account suspension for non-compliant subordinates.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Personnel
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Must complete all assigned training modules and simulations by the defined deadlines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Must apply training concepts to daily operations and report security anomalies immediately.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Condition of Access
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Training completion is a prerequisite for system access.
 Access shall be denied or revoked for any individual without verified training records.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Account Suspension
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Information Operations Department must disable the network account of any user who fails to complete the annual refresher training within 365 days of their last completion.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Exceptions must be documented in writing and approved by the IT Director.
 No exceptions are permitted regarding the requirement to be trained prior to initial CJIS access.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
