\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Program Design and Authority
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall design the curriculum,
 while HR shall manage the administration and tracking of the General Security Awareness Program.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Training Cadence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Initial Training
\series default
:
 Must be completed prior to receiving initial system access.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Annual Refresher
\series default
:
 Must be completed every 365 days.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Event Retraining
\series default
:
 Involved personnel must complete remedial training within 30 days of a major security event per CJIS AT-2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Literacy Content
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The General Security Awareness program must cover:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Insider Threat
\series default
:
 Recognizing indicators of malicious or accidental threat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Social Engineering
\series default
:
 Identifying phishing and vishing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data Handling
\series default
:
 Procedures for CJI and PII protection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Role-Based Training
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Privileged users and physical security personnel shall receive targeted training relevant to their specific technical or environmental duties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Practical Exercises
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department shall conduct not fewer than two (2) spear-phishing simulations annually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Records Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Training records must be retained for a minimum of three (3) years.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Separated personnel records shall be held for 3 years from date of separation (LRDA 20070048).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
General IT awareness records shall be held for 3 years from date of access termination (LRDA 20071725).
\end_layout

